response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Fibonacci Sequence\", \"description\": \"The Fibonacci sequence is a series of numbers where each number is the sum of the two preceding ones, usually starting with 0 and 1. Write a function `fibonacci` that takes an integer `n` as input and returns the nth number in the Fibonacci sequence.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef fibonacci(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): An integer greater than or equal to 0.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the nth number in the Fibonacci sequence.\\n\", \"code\": \"\\ndef fibonacci(n: int) -> int:\\n    if n <= 1:\\n        return n\\n    else:\\n        a, b = 0, 1\\n        for _ in range(2, n+1):\\n            a, b = b, a + b\\n        return b\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert fibonacci(0) == 0\", \"assert fibonacci(1) == 1\", \"assert fibonacci(2) == 1\", \"assert fibonacci(3) == 2\", \"assert fibonacci(10) == 55\"] }"
